      "writtenOn": "2020-09-28T15:11:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the simpleness would have been nearly a wash, the Go code would no longer have had the branches for \u0027is this a task, taskspec, or commit comment\u0027, but that pattern would then have to have been added on the client side to for \u0027should I send a AddTaskComment, AddTaskSpecComment, or AddCommitComment request\u0027, and fill them in correctly.  Mainly kept them together because they have more alike than the do different, and it reuse code this way.",
